data.description: Experience the charm of The Oaks at Appalachia Farm, a prestigious swim, tennis, and golf course community that welcomes you home. This exquisite brick residence, features a three-car garage, promises to captivate you from the moment you step through the front door. Natural light bathes every corner, including the spacious basement. Enter through a grand two-story foyer adorned with tile and hardwood flooring. To the left, a sizable dining room awaits, boasting crown molding, wainscoting, floor-to-ceiling windows, and a dazzling new chandelier. Throughout the home, new light fixtures add a touch of modern elegance. Revel in the bar area conveniently situated between the kitchen and dining room. The kitchen itself is a masterpiece, showcasing white cabinets, granite countertops, and a distinctive curved breakfast bar. Two pantries provide ample storage. Admire the high ceilings in the eat-in kitchen and transition seamlessly into the step-down family room. Here, a newly renovated wood-burning fireplace and coffered ceiling create a cozy atmosphere. Step out onto the private balcony. The main level also features a newly renovated half bathroom with a stylish vanity. Ascend the stairs to discover a spacious master bedroom with tray ceilings, an additional sitting area, and a dual-sided fireplace shared with the luxurious master bathroom. The master bath boasts vaulted ceilings, a separate shower, jacuzzi spa tub, dual vanity sinks, and a generously sized walk-in closet with French doors. Convenience meets luxury with the centrally located laundry room in the hallway, serving three additional bedrooms. Two bedrooms share a Jack and Jill bathroom, while the third has its own en-suite bathroom. The terrace daylight basement opens up a world of possibilities with a separate entrance, kitchen area (stubbed for a sink and cooktop), a workout room behind new barn doors, a craft room with extensive shelving, a bedroom, and a full bathroom adorned with custom tile. The den in the basement features tray ceilings and a custom-built area perfect for an office. Step outside onto the walkout stone patio and a spacious deck in the backyard. A wrought-iron fence encloses the yard, offering a picturesque view of the golf course. The property is equipped with a sprinkler system to keep the yard and flower garden lush and vibrant. This home exudes grace and class, with new HVAC, a new sump pump, and appliances all under five years old. As a bonus, the home comes with a one-year warranty, providing peace of mind and completing the allure of this exceptional residence.
